cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing visual cues in profile pictures to predict the ambiance of places. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of social-networking sites for choosing restaurants and coffee shops. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper explores how people make decisions based on visual cues and how a state-of-the-art algorithm can make predictions more accurately than humans. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of descriptions and reviews on social-networking sites to choose places. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper analyzes visual cues in profile pictures.
